        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): emit non-empty value schema for bitable write tools (#94547)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #94547.\n\nThe Feishu bitable write tools (`feishu_bitable_create_record`, `feishu_bitable_update_record`, `feishu_bitable_create_field`) declare their free-form field maps with `Type.Record(Type.String(), Type.Any(), { ... })`. TypeBox `1.1.39` serializes the `Type.Any()` value schema to an empty object, producing:\n\n```json\n{ \"type\": \"object\", \"patternProperties\": { \"^.*$\": {} } }\n```\n\nAWS Bedrock's strict tool-schema validation rejects the empty nested sub-schema (`{}`), which fails the provider request and can block **all** agent turns for Bedrock-backed Anthropic users who have the Feishu bitable tools enabled. The Bedrock Converse runtime forwards plugin tool `parameters` straight into `toolSpec.inputSchema.json`, and there is no Anthropic/Bedrock provider-side schema normalizer that would repair this (only `deepseek`/`gemini`/`openai` families have schema compat repair).\n\n## Fix\n\nIntroduce one shared, explicit non-empty value schema and use it for the three affected field maps:\n\n```ts\nconst FlexibleFieldValue = Type.Unsafe<unknown>({\n  type: [\"string\", \"number\", \"boolean\", \"object\", \"array\", \"null\"],\n});\n```\n\nThis still accepts any JSON value but serializes to a non-empty nested schema:\n\n```json\n{ \"type\": \"object\", \"patternProperties\": { \"^.*$\": { \"type\": [\"string\",\"number\",\"boolean\",\"object\",\"array\",\"null\"] } } }\n```\n\n`Type.Unknown()` is intentionally **not** used because it serializes to the same empty `{}` schema. `Type.Unsafe<unknown>(...)` is an existing idiom in this repo (e.g. `extensions/feishu/src/chat-schema.ts`, `src/agents/tools/cron-tool.ts`).\n\nAdds regression coverage in `extensions/feishu/src/bitable.test.ts` asserting that each of the three write tools emits a non-empty `patternProperties` value schema.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nEnvironment: macOS arm64, Node v22.22.2, `typebox@1.1.39` (the repo's pinned version), `pnpm@11.2.2`.\n\n**1. Emitted schema, before vs after** (serialized with the repo's bundled TypeBox):\n\n```\nBEFORE (Type.Any value): {\"type\":\"object\",\"patternProperties\":{\"^.*$\":{}}}\nAFTER  (FlexibleFieldValue): {\"type\":\"object\",\"patternProperties\":{\"^.*$\":{\"type\":[\"string\",\"number\",\"boolean\",\"object\",\"array\",\"null\"]}}}\n```\n\nThe \"before\" output reproduces exactly the empty nested schema from the bug report; \"after\" is non-empty.\n\n**2. Regression test inspects the real registered tool parameters** (not a mock) and asserts non-empty value schemas. Test run:\n\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/bitable.test.ts\n ✓ extension-feishu  extensions/feishu/src/bitable.test.ts (5 tests) 8ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  5 passed (5)\n```\n\n**3. Related provider/runtime suites from the issue's acceptance criteria pass:**\n\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts \\\n    extensions/amazon-bedrock/stream.runtime.test.ts \\\n    src/agents/tool-schema-projection.test.ts \\\n    src/llm/providers/stream-wrappers/anthropic-family-tool-payload-compat.test.ts\n ✓ tool-schema-projection.test.ts (10 tests)\n ✓ anthropic-family-tool-payload-compat.test.ts (16 tests)\n ✓ amazon-bedrock/stream.runtime.test.ts (20 tests)\n ✓ plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts\n```\n\n## What I did NOT test\n\n- **No live AWS Bedrock API call was made** — I do not have a Bedrock-backed environment. The provider rejection is supported by (a) the reporter's exact Bedrock validation error in #94547, (b) the source-level reproduction of the empty emitted schema above, and (c) the Bedrock Converse runtime forwarding tool `parameters` into `inputSchema.json`. Happy to add anything else maintainers want here.\n- `oxfmt`/full `pnpm check` were not run locally (the platform formatter binary did not install in my environment); the change follows the surrounding file style.\n",
        "branch": "fix/feishu-bitable-empty-schema",
